Create a schedule to apply to your call settings in the calling user portal
You can create schedules that allow you to apply specific call settings at different times of the day or days of the week. Once your schedules are created, you can select to apply those schedules to your selective call settings, simultaneous ring settings, and/or priority alerts.
1
Go to https://settings.webex.com and select Webex Calling.
2
From the Calling User Portal, go to Call Settings > Schedules.
3
Click New Schedule.
4
Enter a Schedule Name.
5
Select the appropriate Start Date/Time and End Date/Time.
6
Check All day event and/or Repeats, if needed.
7
Click Save.
Example
Want to see how it's done? Watch this video demonstration on how to create schedules for your calling settings in the calling user portal.
What to do next
Now that your schedule is created, you can apply it to your selective call settings, priority alerts, and/or your simultaneous ring settings.